cord by a huge margin setted by Blackpink “How You Like That” having 1.65 Million viewers.</h3><h2 style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color:#E600231">2.</span> Most viewed Youtube video within 24 hours</h2><br><center><img src="d1.webp" class="img-thumbnail " width="60%" height="50%" alt="5-Records-BTS-Broked-With-Dynamite"></center><h3>  After 1 and some hours laters of the BTS “Dynamite” airing, Youtube officialy announced that the BTS “Dynamite” is the by far the most viewed youtube video within 24 hours in the history of youtube having havin 101.1 million views(in 24 hours).</h3><h2 style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color:#E600231">3.</span> Take over the Spotify</h2><h3>YouTube is not the only place where BTS and Army smashed a record with “Dynamite.” According to the sources on Aug. 21, “Dynamite” debuted at No. 1 on Spotify’s daily Global Top 50 chart.The song beated Taylor Swift’s previous record of 7.742 million by achieving 7,778,950 streams within a day with “Dynamite.”</h3><h2 style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color:#E600231">4.</span> Trending #1 on the iTunes Top Songs Chart in 104 countries.</h2><h3>If we have to say the platform the youtube smashed after taking over youtube the names comes into mind is iTunes. “Dynamite” trends as #1 on the iTunes Top Songs Chart in 104 countries, including India and the United States.</h3><h2 style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color:#E600231">5.</span> Perfect All-Kill of Awards in Korean Charts</h2><h3>Now, coming to latest news 31 Aug 200, “Dynamite” is a #1 position in all the top Korean music charts.<br>#1 MelOn<br>#1 Genie<br>#1 FLO<br>#1 Bugs<br>#1 VIBE<br></h3><br><h3 style="text-align:center">“Share article on”</h3><center style="font-size:25px;"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.top2tenasia.xyz/5-Records-BTS-Broked-With-Dynamite" target="_blank" st